 Modern |publisher = Houghton Mifflin Books |year = 2001|isbn = 978-0-395-65237-4|ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book| last = Tabatabaei | first = Sayyid Mohammad Hosayn |authorlink = Allameh Tabatabaei | title = Shi'ite Islam | publisher=Suny press | year = 1979 |isbn = 978-0-87395-272-9|ref = harv}}| Translated by [[Seyyed Hossein Nasr]].\n* {{cite book| last = Tabatabaei| first = Sayyid Mohammad Hosayn| title = The Quran in Islam: Its Impact and Influence on the Life of Muslims| publisher = Zahra| year = 1987| isbn = 978-0-7103-0265-6| url = https://archive.org/details/quraninislamitsi0000taba| ref = harv| url-status = dead| df = dmy-all| url-access = registration}}\n* {{cite book|last = Watt |first = William Montgomery |authorlink = William Montgomery Watt |\ntitle = Muhammad at Mecca | publisher = Oxford University Press |year = 1953 |id =|ref = harv|title-link = Muhammad at Mecca (book) }}\n* {{cite book|last = Zeitlin|first = Irving M.|title = The Historical Muhammad|publisher = Polity|year = 2007|isbn = 978-0-7456-3998-7|ref = harv}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n{{Refbegin|colwidth=30em}}\n\n===Original sources===\n* {{cite book|last = Al-Bukhari |first = Muhammad |title = Sahih Bukhari, Book 4, 5, 8 |id =|authorlink = Muhammad al-Bukhari }}\n* {{cite book|last = Ali ibn Abi Talib | title = Nahj al-Balagha (Peak of Eloquence), compiled by ash-Sharif ar-Radi | year = 1984 | publisher = Alhoda UK |isbn = 978-0-940368-43-9}}\n* {{cite book|last = [[Ali ibn al-Athir]]|title = In his Biography, vol 2 }}\n* {{cite book|last = [[Ibn Taymiyyah]]|first = Taqi ad-Din Ahmad|title = Minhaj as-Sunnah an-Nabawiyyah|id = |title-link = Minhaj as-Sunnah an-Nabawiyyah}} (In Arabic)\n* {{cite book|last = [[Muslim ibn al-Hajjaj]]|title = Sahih Muslim, Book 19, 31| id = }}\n\n===Secondary sources===\n; Books\n* {{cite book| last = Abdul Rauf | first = Muhammad |\ntitle = Imam 'Ali ibn Abi Talib: The First Intellectual Muslim Thinker | author2 = Seyyed Hossein Nasr | publisher = Al S