 Imams|Twelver Imam]]{{-}}[[Zaidiyyah|Zaidi]] [[Imam]]{{-}}[[Kaysanites|Kaysanite]] [[Imam]]{{-}}[[Batiniyya|Batini]] [[List of Isma'ili imams|Isma'ili Imam]]|years=632\u2013661}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[Hasan ibn Ali]]|as=Imam|rows=2}}\n{{S-ttl|title=As\u0101s/W\u0101sih{{-}}in [[Musta'li]] [[Isma'ilism]]|years=632\u2013661}}\n{{S-break}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Nizari]] [[List of Isma'ili imams|Isma'ili Imam]]|years=632\u2013661|rows=2}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[Hasan ibn Ali]]|as=Mustawda}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[Husayn ibn Ali]]|as=Imam}}\n{{S-off}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[Muhammad]]}}\n{{S-tul|title=[[Succession to Muhammad|Successor to Muhammad]]|years=632\u2013656}}\n{{S-non|reason=Election to Caliphate}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[Uthman|Uthman ibn Affan]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Rashidun|Rashidun Caliph]]|years=656\u2013661}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[Hasan ibn Ali]]}}\n{{S-other|Tribal titles}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[Abbas ibn Abd al-Muttalib]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=Chief of [[Banu Hashim]]|years=653\u2013661}}\n{{S-aft|after=?}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Rashidun Caliphs}}\n{{Shia Imams}}\n\n{{Ten companions of Muhammad}}\n{{Ali's companions}}\n{{Islam topics|state = collapsed}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ali}}\n[[Category:Ali| ]]\n[[Category:Rashidun caliphs]]\n[[Category:People from Mecca]]\n[[Category:Arab politicians]]\n[[Category:Assassinated caliphs]]\n[[Category:Arab generals]]\n[[Category:Family of Muhammad]]\n[[Category:Sunni Islam]]\n[[Category:Shia Islam]]\n[[Category:601 births]]\n[[Category:661 deaths]]\n[[Category:7th-century caliphs]]\n[[Category:Shia imams]]\n[[Category:Assassinated Shia imams]]\n[[Category:Twelver imams]]\n[[Category:Zaidi imams]]\n[[Category:7th-century judges]]\n[[Category:7th-century Arabs]]\n[[Category:Arab Muslims]]\n[[Category:Muslim writers]]\n[[Category:Converts to Islam]]\n[[Category:Deaths by blade weapons]]\n[[Category:Muslim martyrs]]\n[[Category:The Fourteen Infallibles]]\n[[Category:Horticulturists and gardeners]]\n[[Category:Philanthropists]]\n[[Category:7th-century rulers in Asia]]\n[[Category:Deified people]]\n[[Category:Ahl al-Kisa]]\n[[Category:Ahl al-Bayt]]\n[[Category:Sahabah favored by Shias]]\n[[Category:Islamic philosophers]]\n[[Category:Sahabah martyrs]]\n[[Category:Sahabah participated in battle of Uhud]]\n[[Category:Sahabah participated in battle of Badr]]\n[[Category:People of the First Fitna]]\n[[Category:Male Sahabah]]\n[[Category:Banu Hashim]]\n", "name_user": "Rizorius", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAssassination in Kufa", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ali"}
{"title_page": "STAG1", "text_new": "{{Infobox_gene}}\n'''Cohesin subunit SA-1''' ('''SA1''') is a [[protein]] that in humans is encoded by the ''STAG1'' [[gene]].<ref name=\"pmid9305759\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Carramolino L, Lee BC, Zaballos A, Peled A, Barthelemy I, Shav-Tal Y, Prieto I, Carmi P, Gothelf Y, Gonz\u00e1lez de Buitrago G, Aracil M, M\u00e1rquez G, Barbero JL, Zipori D | title = SA-1, a nuclear protein encoded by one member of a novel gene family: molecular cloning and detection in hemopoietic organs | journal = Gene | volume = 195 | issue = 2 | pages = 151\u20139 | date = August 1997 | pmid = 9305759 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1016/S0378-1119(97)00121-2 }}</ref><ref name=\"entrez\">{{cite web | title = Entrez Gene: STAG1 stromal antigen 1| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=gene&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=10274| accessdate = }}</ref>\n\n== Function ==\n\nThis gene is a member of the SCC3 family and is expressed in the nucleus. It encodes a component of cohesin, a multisubunit protein complex that provides sister chromatid cohesion along the length of a chromosome from DNA replication through prophase and prometaphase, after which it is dissociated in preparation for segregation during anaphase.<ref name=\"entrez\"/>\n\n== Interactions ==\n\nSTAG1 has been shown to [[Protein-protein interaction|interact]] with [[STAG2]].<ref name=pmid11076961>{{cite journal | vauthors = Sumara I, Vorlaufer E, Gieffers C, Peters BH, Peters JM | title = Characterization of vertebrate cohesin complexes and their regulation in prophase | journal = The Journal of Cell Biology | volume = 151 | issue = 4 | pages = 749\u201362 | date = November 2000 | pmid = 11076961 | pmc = 2169443 | doi = 10.1083/jcb.151.4.749 }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin | 2}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Kimura K, Wakamatsu A, Suzuki Y, Ota T, Nishikawa T, Yamashita R, Yamamoto J, Sekine M, Tsuritani K, Wakaguri H, Ishii S, Sugiyama T, Saito K, Isono Y, Irie R, Kushida N, Yoneyama T, Otsuka R, Kanda K, Yokoi T, Kondo H, Wagatsuma M, Murakawa K, Ishida S, Ishibashi T, Takahashi-Fujii A, Tanase T, Nagai K, Kikuchi H, Nakai K, Isogai T, Sugano S | title = Diversification of transcriptional modulation: large-scale identification and characterization of putative alternative promoters of human genes | journal = Genome Research | volume = 16 | issue = 1 | pages = 55\u201365 | date = January 2006 | pmid = 16344560 | pmc = 1356129 | doi = 10.1101/gr.4039406 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Losada A, Yokochi T, Hirano T | title = Functional contribution of Pds5 to cohesin-mediated cohesion in human cells and Xenopus egg extracts | journal = Journal of Cell Science | volume = 118 | issue = Pt 10 | pages = 2133\u201341 | date = May 2005 | pmid = 15855230 | doi = 10.1242/jcs.02355 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Anazawa Y, Arakawa H, Nakagawa H, Nakamura Y | title = Identification of STAG1 as a key mediator of a p53-dependent apoptotic pathway | journal = Oncogene | volume = 23 | issue = 46 | pages = 7621\u20137 | date = October 2004 | pmid = 15361841 | doi = 10.1038/sj.onc.1207270 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Prieto I, Pezzi N, Buesa JM, Kremer L, Barthelemy I, Carreiro C, Roncal F, Martinez A, Gomez L, Fernandez R, Martinez-A C, Barbero JL | title = STAG2 and Rad21 mammalian mitotic cohesins are implicated in meiosis | journal = EMBO Reports | volume = 3 | issue = 6 | pages = 543\u201350 | date = June 2002 | pmid = 12034751 | pmc = 1084142 | doi = 10.1093/embo-reports/kvf108 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Gregson HC, Schmiesing JA, Kim JS, Kobayashi T, Zhou S, Yokomori K | title = A potential role for human cohesin in mitotic spindle aster assembly | journal = The Journal of Biological Chemistry | volume = 276 | issue = 50 | pages = 47575\u201382 | date = December 2001 | pmid = 11590136 | doi = 10.1074/jbc.M103364200 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Sumara I, Vorlaufer E, Gieffers C, Peters BH,